Vice President Mike Pence delivers a speech at Santa Catarina Church in Manaus, Brazil, expressing support for the people of Venezuela and their struggle for democracy. He condemns the Maduro regime for its suppression of political dissent, violence against protestors, and economic mismanagement. Pence reassures the Venezuelan families who have fled to Brazil that the United States stands with them and will continue to provide support. He also commends Brazil and other nations in the region for their efforts in providing shelter and safety to Venezuelan refugees. Pence expresses faith in the strength of the Venezuelan people and the international community's commitment to restoring freedom in Venezuela.